Thirdparty Software
=====================

ViMbAdmin includes some other thirdparty software in its distribution:

bin/yuicompressor.jar - released under the BSD license but in itself also
       contains code under Mozilla Public License (MPL). See:
       http://developer.yahoo.com/yui/compressor/

bin/compiler.jar - a Java command-line utility that compresses, optimizes,
       and looks for mistakes in your JavaScript. Released under the
       Apache License Version 2.0. See:
       http://code.google.com/p/closure-compiler/

public/js-dev/08-superfish.js - jQuery menu widget. Dual licensed under
       the MIT and GPL licenses.

public/js-dev/08-vimbadmin.tooltip.js - a jQuery tool tip.Licensed under
       the MIT license.

public/js-dev/
       01-jquery.js - JQuery - http://jquery.com/ - MIT/GPL
       02-jquery-ui.js - JQuery UI - http://jqueryui.com/ - MIT/GPL
       03-jquery-validate.js - JQuery Validator - MIT/GPL http://bassistance.de/jquery-plugins/jquery-plugin-validation/
       07-jquery-colorbox.js - ColorBox - MIT
       09-jquery-datatables.js JQuery Datatables - http://www.datatables.net - GPL/MIT


In addition, Doctrine, Zend Framework and Smarty are used from SVN externals.
